# NOTE: config.js is committed so GitHub Pages can serve it.
# Firebase web API keys are designed to be public — they identify the project,
# not authenticate it. Real security comes from Firestore rules + the house
# code being known only to your group. If you ever change hosting and want to
# keep config.js out of git, just add `config.js` back to this file.

